vim usage:

    git clone https://github.com/zhaojunbo/dotfiles.git ~/.files
    cd ~/.files
    git submodule init
    git submodule update
    ln -sf ~/.files/.vim ~/.vim
    ln -sf ~/.vim/.vimrc ~/.vimrc


Then let Vundle take over:

    vim ~/.vimrc
    :BundleInstall


In order to use NERDTree, try <Ctrl+E> in vim console.


In order to use tag-bar, try <F8>; but you should have exuberant-cTags installed. Basically, on Linux/Mac systems the default ctags is probably the basic ctags (useless! :( ), not exuberant-cTags (Use ctags --version to see what your default ctags is). So you have to rearrange your PATH by: 
    PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH
    which ctags
Browse [here] for more infomation about exuberant-cTags installation and setting.
